    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 22 article about recent layoffs at Internet companies</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article and chart in Business Day yesterday about recent layoffs at Internet companies misstated the status of one company, APBnews.com. Although it announced on June 5 that it was out of money and was laying off all 140 employees, it has continued operations, recently found new financing and hired back about 30 workers.</p>
        <p>In addition, the chart misstated the number of employees laid off by Salon.com. It was 13, not 19.</p>
      </block>
